==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shunt winding
<hw>Shunt winding</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A winding so arranged as
to divide the armature current and lead a portion of it around the
field-magnet coils; -- opposed to <contr>series winding</contr>.</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>Shunt"-wound`</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shut</ent>⟦br⟧
